{"id":"elam","term":"Elam","source":"International Standard Bible Encyclopaedia (James Orr ed., 1915)","html":"<p>e'-lam (`elam):</p><p>(1) A son of Shem (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 10:22\">Ge 10:22</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 1:17\">1Ch 1:17</a>; see ELAMITES).</p><p>(2) A Benjamite (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 8:24\">1Ch 8:24</a>).</p><p>(3) A Korahite (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 26:3\">1Ch 26:3</a>).</p><p>(4) Heads of families in the return (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 2:7\">Ezr 2:7</a> parallel <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 7:12\">Ne 7:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 2:31\">Ezr 2:31</a> parallel <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 7:34\">Ne 7:34</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 8:7\">Ezr 8:7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 10:2\">10:2</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 10:26\">26</a>).</p><p>(5) A chief of the people (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 10:14\">Ne 10:14</a>).</p><p>(6) A priest (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 12:42\">Ne 12:42</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 10:22","1 Chronicles 1:17","1 Chronicles 8:24","1 Chronicles 26:3","Ezra 2:7","Nehemiah 7:12","Ezra 2:31","Nehemiah 7:34","Ezra 8:7","Ezra 10:2","Ezra 10:26","Nehemiah 10:14","Nehemiah 12:42"]}